public interface Editable
This class defines objects that can be edited in GOAL. Each editable object is associated with a set of properties obtained by getProperties(). Some properties of an editable object may be built-in, that is, the properties exist when this object is designed. With the default codec GFFCodec in GOAL, all string properties of an editable object supported by the codec will be stored.
Author:
Ming-Hsien Tsai
